{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/opioid-dependence/diagnosis/suspecting-opioid-dependency/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"ee9cab5c-4665-56a2-9005-028143cc8f59","slug":"suspecting-opioid-dependency","fullItemName":"Suspecting opioid dependency","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 109b8a96-250d-4d1a-aa6b-2fa901ef20f9 --><h2>When should I suspect a person has a problem with opioid dependency?</h2><!-- end field 109b8a96-250d-4d1a-aa6b-2fa901ef20f9 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 95a205ba-22f7-444d-a4d4-d54a0438ad08 --><!-- begin field 5355a2c2-0579-479f-b374-73c495cb3dc0 --><ul><li><strong>Drug misuse may become apparent while a person is consulting with another medical problem (that may or may not be drug-related), or present in a variety of ways:</strong><ul><li><strong>An active request for help with:</strong><ul><li>Drug dependency — the user has realized that there are problems associated with taking drugs, or has become motivated to change behaviour, or a crisis has developed (perhaps as a result of an impending court case, health or relationship problems).</li><li>Alcohol dependency — always ask about drug misuse.</li></ul></li><li><strong>A <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/opioid-dependence/background-information/complications/\">complication</a> of drug use.</strong></li><li><strong>Clinical features of opioid intoxication </strong>— symptoms and signs include:<ul><li>Constriction of pupils, itching and scratching, sedation and somnolence, lower blood pressure, slower pulse, hypoventilation. </li></ul></li><li><strong>Acute withdrawal syndrome</strong> — symptoms and signs include: <ul><li>Watering eyes, rhinorrhoea, yawning, sneezing, cool and clammy skin, dilated pupils, cough.</li><li>Abdominal cramps, nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea.</li><li>Tremor, sleep disorder, restlessness, anxiety, irritability, hypertension.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Certain features:</strong><ul><li>Psychiatric history — overdoses, depression, psychosis.</li><li>Forensic history — past custodial sentences, probation, community service.</li><li>Social history — family problems, unemployment, accommodation issues, financial problems.</li></ul></li><li>On physical examination, there may be evidence of poor nutrition, dental caries, other signs of neglect, needle tracks, skin abscess, and signs of drug intoxication or withdrawal. </li><li>On mental health assessment, there may be indications of abnormal general behaviour, disorders of mood (particularly anxiety or low mood), delusions or hallucinations, confusion.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 5355a2c2-0579-479f-b374-73c495cb3dc0 --><!-- end item 95a205ba-22f7-444d-a4d4-d54a0438ad08 -->","topic":{"id":"ef534296-f504-5d3e-9b47-3c0f08322658","topicId":"1acd30d9-6aea-492b-a570-5fbeb05d49f5","topicName":"Opioid dependence","slug":"opioid-dependence","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2020","chapters":[{"id":"7b9e0e1a-3aea-5219-a001-dfd22a786292","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a0179729-bb50-55a3-a1dc-ca3cbd473972","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e63e1346-068d-56e6-891b-85878800d361","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"37edcefe-2b9f-5ab8-a584-be9e268559ac","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"b53b49f5-e58d-5325-8fee-7f9fdc057646","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"242f440f-b9b5-51a4-9d43-3492e963e9af","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"5766349b-04fe-548c-9de5-0ff28c7803b9","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"2ed8ffe3-15a2-5e49-b2ad-033e1a4b5f22","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"419add6c-5149-5bbf-9be1-8854fefbccc4","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemNam